===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[Dutch]] [[tilt]]}}

#{{cattag|Filmology}}: A [[cinematic]] tactic achieved by [[tilt]]ing the [[camera]] off to the side. The [[shot]] is [[compose]]d with the [[horizon]] not [[parallel]] with the bottom of the [[frame]].  The technique is often used to portray the psychological uneasiness of the subject being filmed.

